Excited to welcome Miguel Mendoza to our team! He's originally from Tri-Cities, Washington. He spends most of his free time adventuring with his 5 year old son and 1 1/2 year old pup and spending time on his self-help podcast! His favorite workouts are pull ups and lunges. Long walks with headphones on are his therapy! IHe is extremely passionate about fitness and athletics. He believes the need for working out goes beyond physical appearance but it also helps with mental health and it teaches us to overcome obstacles which we carry over to all aspect of our lives! 
Welcome Miguel!

Super excited to welcome Auggie Moser to the RDFiT Team!  Auggie was born and raised in a small town of rural Wisconsin; where He attended high school and later moved on to get his Bachelors degree in Kinesiology from the University of Wisconsin Eau-Claire. His goal is simple: meet each client where theyre at and help them Flourish- to actualize their potential- on the pursuit to lasting lifestyle change. 
Welcome Auggie!

Are you tired of feeling tired?

Have you been thinking that you need to take control of your health before it takes control of you?

RDFit is here to help! 
Try our FREE Boot Camp Class and learn the skills you need to start living a healthier life TODAY!

Our coaches will bring together incredible workouts, nutritious meal plans, and tips for how to stick with your healthy habits even when the going gets tough. It's never too late to start making positive changes in your life and whether you're looking to lose weight, get toned, or just feel better about yourself, we can help.

ABSOLUTELY FREE and open to everyone, but space is limited, so grab your spot NOW! 

Click here to reserve a spot: https://clients.mindbodyonline.com/classic/mainclass
